****************************Pseudocode***********************************

Import the scanner class.
Create scanner object and assign it to input var.
Prompt user for 10 words separated by space
Store the input in a string variable.
Then split the string with regular expresion " " and store it in a string array.
Use Bubble sort
    create a for loop to iterate through the string array
        creat an inner for loop to compare the next array
            use an if statement to compare two strings
            swap if true
        iterate till the array end
     repeat till no more to swap
Print out the result
    use for loop to iterate and print out the array in order

Print array in reversed order
    use for loop to iterate from the end of the array to the start

*************************** Test Cases **********************************
Enter 10 words separated by space:
kiwi pineapple apple banana orange grapes watermelon dog ear day
Original order:
kiwi pineapple apple banana orange grapes watermelon dog ear day

Alphabetical Order:
apple banana day dog ear grapes kiwi orange pineapple watermelon

Reversed Alphabetical Order:
watermelon pineapple orange kiwi grapes ear dog day banana apple